The paper deals with the problem of semi-supervised learning of image classifiers, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a framework that unifies self-supervised visual representation learning and semi-supervised learning, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Finally, the paper uses neural networks for its experiments, which is a topic that falls under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
